About DataTypes:-
What is a DataType?
DataType is Specifies the Different sizes and values can be Stored in a Variable.They are two Data Types in Java
PRIMITIVE DATA TYPES:-byte,short,int,long,float,double,char,boolean
REFERENCE DATA TYPES:-classes,interfaces,arrays

Primitive Data Types in Java:-
In java language Primitive Data Types are main building blocks of Data Manipulations.These are most useful Data Types available in java Language.

They are 8 Primitive Data Types in java

S.NO          DATA TYPE                         DEFAULT SIZE(BYTES)                  DEFAULT VALUE                   VALUE RANGE
 1              byte                                1                                       0                        -2^7 - 2^7-1
 2              short                               2                                       0                       -2^15 - 2^15-1
 3               int                                4                                       0                       -2^31 - 2^31-1
 4              long                                8                                       0L                      -2^63 - 2^63-1
 5              float                               4                                       0.0f                    -3.4e38 - 3.4e38
 6              double                              8                                       0.0d                    -1.7e308 - 1.7e308
 7              char                                2                                      '\u0000'                     0-65535
 8              boolean                             1(Bit)                                  false                 Not applicable but allowed values are true or false

